quran[29]{c,v,t,f}:
91,1,"By the sun and its heat and brightness, {1}",footnotes:1:The word duha as used in the original applies both to the light of the sun and to its heat. Although in Arabic its well known meaning is the time between sunrise and meridian when the sun has risen high
91,2,"and by the moon as it follows it;"
91,3,"and by the day as it displays the sun's glory,"
91,4,"and by the night as it envelopes the sun; {1}",footnotes:1:That is
91,5,"and by the sky and by Him Who made it; {1}",footnotes:1:Who established it: Who established it like a vault over the earth. In this verse and in the two succeeding verses
91,6,"and by the earth and by Him Who stretched it out;"
91,7,"and by the soul and by Him Who perfectly proportioned it, {1}",footnotes:1:Proportioned it: Gave man such a body which by virtue of its erect stature
91,8,"and imbued it with (the consciousness of) its evil and its piety: {1}",footnotes:1:The word ilham is derived from lahm which means to swallow. According to this very basic meaning
91,9,"He who purifies it will prosper,"
91,10,"and he who suppresses it will be ruined. {1}",footnotes:1:This is for which an oath has been sworn by the things mentioned in the above verses. Let us now consider how those things bear upon it. The rule that Allah has followed in the Quran is that to bear testimony to the truth that He wants to impress on the human mind
91,11,"In their presumptuous insolence the Thamud {1} called the Truth a lie {2}",footnotes:1:The things stated in principle in the above verses are now being explained by an historical precedent. Of what it is a precedent and how it relates to what has been stated above
91,12,"when their arch-criminal rose up in rage."
91,13,"Then Allah's Messenger warned them: “Hands off the she-camel and her drink!” {1}",footnotes:1:At other places in the Quran the following details
91,14,"But they rejected his statement as a lie and hamstrung the she-camel. {1} For that crime their Lord rumbled down upon them, utterly razing them to the ground.",footnotes:1:According to (Surah Al-Aaraf
91,15,"He has no fear of its sequel. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
92,1,"By the night when it enshrouds,"
92,2,"and by the day when it breaks in its glory,"
92,3,"and by Him Who created the male and the female:"
92,4,"surely your strivings are divergent. {1}",footnotes:1:This is that for which an oath has been sworn by the night and the day
92,5,"As for him who gave out his wealth (for Allah's sake) and abstained (from disobeying Him),"
92,6,"and affirmed the Truth of goodness: {1}",footnotes:1:This is the first kind of endeavors
92,7,"We shall facilitate for him the Way to Bliss. {1}",footnotes:1:This is the result of the first kind of endeavoring and struggling. The easy way implies the way which is in accordance with human nature
92,8,"As for him who was a miser and behaved with aversion (to Allah),"
92,9,"and denied the Truth of goodness: {1}",footnotes:1:This is the second kind of human endeavoring
92,10,"We shall facilitate for him the way to Hardship, {1}",footnotes:1:This way has been called the hard way
92,11,"and his wealth shall be of no avail to him when he perishes. {1}",footnotes:1:In other words it means that he has to die one day and leave behind in the world whatever he had amassed for his ease and enjoyment. If he did not earn and send forward something for the Hereafter
92,12,"Surely it is for Us to show the Right Way, {1}",footnotes:1:That is
92,13,"and to Us belong the Next Life and the present. {1}",footnotes:1:This statement has several meanings and all are correct:
92,14,"I have now warned you of a Blazing Fire,"
